snippet.textDisplay: I recently got horrible acne and absolutely could not get rid of it for two years. Never had acne my entire life until 20 years old. WTF! I tried everything, at least I thought. After diving through ridiculous amounts of research, I decided to cut out foods that were likely to upset my stomach/body easily. I didn’t think I had very bad digestion at the time. I was very regular, but what I didn't realize was that I wasn't digesting my food well. I also didn't have many stomach aches, mostly just an uncomfortably full feeling after I ate and feeling really tired and fatigued too. I found out that I have sensitivities to gluten and corn. I highly recommend you try taking a look at the foods you eat and determining if maybe one or some of them are causing your acne. It's a long road to recovery. It took me about two month of cutting out those foods and taking probiotic+L-glutamine to get rid of my acne. Good luck, Emma! I hope you can find out what is causing it. You probably won't read this, but if you do, I hope you’ll consider it.
